[Cases continue to be reported for a total now of 1053 laboratory-confirmed listeriosis cases, 20 more cases than last reported by ProMED-mail in May 2018, with a case fatality rate of 20 percent. The source, "polony" contaminated with the outbreak strain of _Listeria moncytogenes_, was recalled in early March 2018. With an incubation period of up to 70 days, at this point, new cases of listeriosis are likely to be due to delays in reporting, or perhaps failure to discard listeria-contaminated polony despite the recall. - Mod.ML

